as·cet·i·cism [ ə séttə sizzəm ] 


noun  
 
self-denying way of life: austerity and self-denial, especially as a principled way of life
 
asceticism (n) 
  
austerity, self-discipline, abstemiousness, self-denial, abstinence, simplicity, severity, starkness, strictness, self-restraint, plainness, frugality, rigor

Antonym: hedonism